The paper deals with binary linear codes and their properties, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC) sub-categories. The use of algebraic-geometry codes and bilinear algebra suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the construction of asymptotically good families of codes may also be of interest to researchers in the area of distributed systems (cs.DS).
